Some hoodlums described as pro-government have set several vehicles on fire in Abuja The arson affected some End SARS protesters’ cars and an auto dealer’s stand. The location is the Apo mechanic village in the nation’s capital. Demonstrations against Police brutality are ongoing nationwide. Monday witnessed several occurrences in different states. There was an attack on police officers in Lagos and a prison break in Benin, Edo State capital. In Abuja and Nyanya in Nasarawa State, policemen assaulted citizens carrying Nigerian flags. Video: At Apo Mechanic Village razed by government hired Thugs #EndSARS pic.twitter.com/x79Pkx66Yr — Fakhrriyyah (@FakhuusHashim) October 19, 2020